@startuml
title Chapter 2.02 - Observer Pattern Class Model

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

package "chapter2/02-observer" {

class TestBuilder {
  +itsECG_Module : ECG_Module
  +itsHistogramDisplay : HistogramDisplay
  +itsTMDQueue : TMDQueue
  --
  +Init()
  +Cleanup()
}

class ECG_Module {
  +dataNum : int
  +lead1 : int
  +lead2 : int
  +itsTMDQueue : TMDQueue*
  --
  +acquireValue()
  +setLeadPair(l1, l2)
}

class TMDQueue {
  +head : int
  +nSubscribers : int
  +size : int
  +buffer[QUEUE_SIZE] : TimeMarkedData
  +itsNotificationHandle : NotificationHandle*
  --
  +insert(tmd)
  +notify(tmd)
  +remove(index)
  +subscribe(updateFuncAddr)
  +unsubscribe(updateFuncAddr)
  +getNextIndex(index)
  +isEmpty()
}

class NotificationHandle {
  +updateAddr : UpdateFuncPtr
  +itsNotificationHandle : NotificationHandle*
}

class HistogramDisplay {
  +index : int
  +itsTMDQueue : TMDQueue*
  --
  +getValue()
  +update(tmd)
  +updateHistogram()
}

class TimeMarkedData {
  +timeInterval : int
  +dataValue : int
  +itsTMDQueue : TMDQueue*
}

class main {
  +main(argc, argv)
}

}

main --> TestBuilder : creates
TestBuilder *-- ECG_Module
TestBuilder *-- HistogramDisplay
TestBuilder *-- TMDQueue

ECG_Module --> TMDQueue : inserts samples into
HistogramDisplay --> TMDQueue : subscribes to
TMDQueue o-- "0..*" NotificationHandle : subscriber list
TMDQueue *-- "QUEUE_SIZE" TimeMarkedData : circular buffer
TimeMarkedData --> TMDQueue : belongs to

note right of TMDQueue
Leaky circular queue:
- new samples overwrite oldest slots
- multiple observers can read the same data
- insert() triggers notify()
end note

note right of NotificationHandle
Each node stores one callback and
links to the next subscriber.
end note

@enduml
